COORD_SYS_NAME: Cartesian 2D CS. Axes: southing, westing (P,M). Orientations: south, west. UoM: m.
REMARKS: Used in old projected coordinate reference systems in Portugal.

COORD_SYS_NAME: Cartesian 2D CS. Axes: plant E, Plant N (x,y). Orientations: northeast, northwest. UoM: m.
REMARKS: Used in engineering coordinate reference systems.

COORD_SYS_NAME: Seismic acquisition bin grid. Axes: Inline, Crossline (I,J). Orientations: Along rx line, across rx line. UoM: 25m x 12.5m.
REMARKS:
Bin grid increment on I axis = 1 bin, bin grid increment on J axis = 1 bin.
By definition, I axis is rotated 90 degrees clockwise from J axis.

COORD_SYS_NAME: Cartesian 3D CS (gravity-related Topocentric). Axes: plant E, Plant N, height (x,y,z). Orientations: east, north, up. UoM: m.
REMARKS: Used in engineering coordinate reference systems. x and y are in the horizontal plane and z is the local vertical. Not to be confused with CS 4461.
